[But the moſt fulſome Courtſhip of Saints I meet with, are thoſe ſtrains that are directed to the Relations of our Saviour according to the fleſh; of whom the Scripture ſpeaks very little, (I except here the Bl. Virgin, whom I at preſent paſs over) it neither tells us any thing of the piety of ſome of them; nor advances any of them in excellency or intereſt with God, above the reſt of the Apoſtles and Diſciples of Chriſt; you cannot but obſerve, that their unſeaſonable interpoſing in matters that related to the office of our Saviour, was repreſſed by him, rather than at all encouraged; as appears by his anſwer to his Parents that found him in the Temple;
                           Luk. 2.49. his anſwer to the people,
                           Luk. 8.21. that told him that his Mother and his Brethren deſired to ſee and ſpeak with him;
                           Joh. 2.4. and his anſwer to the Bl. Virgin her ſelf, at the Marriage-Feaſt at Canà, when they wanted Wine. Yet ſuch is the boldneſs (I may ſay prophaneneſs) of theſe worſhippers of Saints, that they repreſent to God and them, as mighty prevailing arguments, the relation and kindred they had to our Saviour,


and upon that account ask the greateſt boons. I'le inſtance only in thoſe to S. Joſeph, and to Joachim and Anna the Parents of the Bl. Virgin.]
